  "response": "No, Microsoft does not own Google. Microsoft and Google are separate, independent companies and are actually competitors in many areas of technology, including search engines, cloud computing, productivity software, and more.\n\nMicrosoft is the company behind products like Windows, Microsoft Office, Azure, and Xbox, while Google (officially under its parent company, Alphabet Inc.) is known for products like Google Search, Android, YouTube, and Google Cloud. Both companies are major players in the tech industry, but they operate independently of each other.",
